Package: orange
Type: Package
Title: Spherical Ranges and Parametrization of Geographic Shapes
Version: 0.1.0-6
Authors@R: c(
	person(given="Adam T.", family="Kocsis", role=c("cre", "aut"),
		   email="adam.t.kocsis@gmail.com", comment=c(ORCID="0000-0002-9028-665X")),
	person(given="FAU GeoZentrum Nordbayern", role="fnd"))
Maintainer: Adam T. Kocsis <adam.t.kocsis@gmail.com>
Description: A collation of tools and metrics to characterize distribution data on the surfrace of a sphere or an ellipsoid. The primary group of these metrics is those that describe the extent of a distribution, i.e. geographic ranges. The calculation of geographic ranges can be executed using point coordinates data, vector polygons, as well as and cells on a discretized sphere. Besides ensuring the use a geometrically correct implementations, the package offers the exploration of partial results for visual diagnostics.
